(A) CS 15 ArrayLists Homework
(B) The purpose of the program is to make a Character Array List and create 
functions that return certain values in each list. Additionally, the functions
will also alter certain characters in the lists. 
(C) I went to office hours to better understand the &operator= function. I
also asked a question on Piazza.
(D) I have provided CharArrayList.h which is a header file for 
CharArrayList.cpp. CharArrayList.cpp has the function definitions for the 
CharArrayLists. I have also provided unit_tests.h, a file that contains 
tests for each function.
(E) By using unit_test.
(F) In my code, my abstract data type is the list of characters, which
inclues operations such as insertion, removal, indexed access, replacement,
and concatenation. The ADT is implemented using an array list, which is
dynamically allocated with variable that track the array's size and capacity.
The structure is constantly updated to allocate for more characters and bigger
lists. I used a dynamic array because it would the easiest structure to use
to create a list that would update and expand when needed to. The main 
advantage is the fast access to the elements in the list. However, the main 
disadvanges are the time of insertions and removals.
(G) I have tested my assignmet by creating tests in unit_tests.h. In these 
tests, I have created edge cases that would give range errors and runtime
errors. Additionally, I have created tests that target the front, back, and
middle of a character array list.
(H) 5 hours
(I) 1. (in nanoseconds) Insertion: Front: 2252909 Back: 477 Middle: 2206020
Removal: Front: 2197134 Back: 2228364 Middle: 1149500
Access: Front: 618 Back: 607 Middle: 420
Fastest to slowest: access, insertion, Removal
2. Some operations were slower than others because they did not use for loops.
To give an example, in my access functions, I don't use a loop and it is the
fastest operation. Inserting and removing take around the same time because
I use for loops to recreate the array list. 